The Weekly Dose of Optimism was founded on the core idea that a lot of real=
ly positive stuff is happening in the world, but for whatever reason, that =
information doesn't make its way into the news cycle. Optimism doesn=E2=80=
=99t usually bleed, so it doesn=E2=80=99t usually lead. So we understand th=
e importance of conveying optimistic stories in a way that=E2=80=99s easily=
 digestible, entertaining, and consumable. We (try to) do that through writ=
ing. But a picture is worth a thousand words =E2=80=94 which is why we were=
 excited to discover information is beautiful [ https://substack.com/redire=
ct/5662ef78-33db-4916-ac6c-bbcce844fa7b?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_Z=
lNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], a website that displays positive news/fa=
cts/trends in beautiful infographics. It=E2=80=99s like Our World in Data [=
 https://substack.com/redirect/97866a8e-ea2e-41a2-8775-b7f25da4a5a8?j=3DeyJ=
1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], but if the c=
harts were designed for Instagram. We highly recommend you spend a moment =
=E2=80=9CProgress Scrolling=E2=84=A2=E2=80=9D before you head off for the w=
eekend.
